'''TestDisk''' is a [[free software]] data recovery utility licensed under the terms of the [[GNU General Public License]] (GPL). It was primarily designed to help recover lost data storage [[Partition (computing)|partitions]] and/or make non-booting disks bootable again when these symptoms are caused by faulty software, certain types of viruses or human error (such as accidentally erasing a partition table).
